Computer Science Legend, Rear Adm. Grace Hopper, Posthumously Receives Presidential Medal of Freedom

By April Grant, Navy Office of Information

WASHINGTON (NNS) -- Rear Adm. Grace Murray Hopper, best known for her advancements in computer programming and data processing, was awarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom posthumously by President Barack Obama during a White House ceremony Nov. 22.
